parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to the risk of airbag inflator explosion, causing serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: No symptoms are reported
as the issue is related to the delay in repairing the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause difficulty stopping the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Hissing noise when the brake pedal is depressed
hard brake pedal
and difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illumination
failure of the passenger's side airbag light to illuminate
and failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to extended stopping distances, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
hissing sounds when pressing the brake pedal
and the ABS warning light may be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel spongy or soft, leading to extended stopping distances, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PTU can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding or whining noise
loss of power
hesitation
or stalling
particularly when shifting gears or driving uphill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Slipping or hesitation when shifting gears
loss of power
or sudden acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Master Cylinder or Slave Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder or slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Soft or spongy clutch pedal
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
or difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding or whining noise
loss of power
or hesitation when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the vehicle to hesitate, stall, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Hesitation
stalling
or loss of power when accelerating.
